This is a demo demonstrating FifeGui and overloading of widgets to get an FPS
look alike menu system.

This demo requires SDL2, SDL2_image, SDL2_mixer, OpenGL, and GLU development headers.

If GLU is missing, install it with your distro package manager:

- Debian/Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install libglu1-mesa-dev
- Fedora: sudo dnf install mesa-libGLU-devel
- Arch: sudo pacman -S glu

=== BUILD ===
This demo is built with the project CMake build system.

From the repository root:

cmake -S . -B out/build
cmake --build out/build --target fps_demo

=== RUN ===
From the repository root:

./out/build/examples/fps/fps_demo

If your environment has no audio device, use:

SDL_AUDIODRIVER=dummy ./out/build/examples/fps/fps_demo

